I don't have
any clean Tupperware.

263
00:13:46.286 --> 00:13:48.621
All right.
definitely next time.

264
00:13:48.663 --> 00:13:51.040
Don't be silly.
Now hold out your hands.

265
00:13:51.082 --> 00:13:53.334
-You want to--
-Do it.

266
00:13:57.046 --> 00:13:58.590
Cool.

267
00:13:58.631 --> 00:13:59.924
Thanks a lot.

268
00:14:03.303 --> 00:14:06.014
Now. please. take a bite...

269
00:14:06.055 --> 00:14:08.099
so that I can
watch you enjoy.

270
00:14:08.141 --> 00:14:10.018
That's my favorite part.

271
00:14:10.059 --> 00:14:13.062
Well...
I'll go with the right one.

272
00:14:13.104 --> 00:14:14.105
That looks good.

273
00:14:19.777 --> 00:14:21.988
That's a good meatball.

274
00:14:22.030 --> 00:14:26.868
Now. listen to me. Robbie Hart.

275
00:14:26.910 --> 00:14:30.079
You're going to be
a fine husband.

276
00:14:30.121 --> 00:14:32.707
I hope so. Rosie. Thank you.

277
00:14:32.749 --> 00:14:34.167
I'm going to leave.

278
00:14:34.209 --> 00:14:35.502
I'll see you
at the wedding. all right?

279
00:14:45.845 --> 00:14:48.389
Thank you for coming in
and taking me to lunch.

280
00:14:48.431 --> 00:14:51.059
Look at the picture
of that girl. See that?

281
00:14:51.100 --> 00:14:53.937
You're a lot prettier
than that girl...

282
00:14:53.978 --> 00:14:55.355
and she's getting married.

283
00:14:55.355 --> 00:14:58.191
What does pretty have to do
with getting married?

284
00:14:58.233 --> 00:15:00.235
Everything.
You got to get married...

285
00:15:00.276 --> 00:15:03.071
before your hips start spreading
and you get facial hair...

286
00:15:03.112 --> 00:15:06.157
which. by the way.
comes from your father's mother.

287
00:15:06.199 --> 00:15:09.202
Looks like Magnum. P.I..
for God's sake.

288
00:15:09.244 --> 00:15:12.288
I can't make Glenn set a date.

289
00:15:12.330 --> 00:15:15.583
You're going to hate
this idea...

290
00:15:15.625 --> 00:15:21.047
but I think you should consider
a fake pregnancy.

291
00:15:21.089 --> 00:15:22.340
I'm exiting the car.

292
00:15:22.382 --> 00:15:23.967
It's just a means to an end.

293
00:15:24.008 --> 00:15:26.302
ln five years.
he'll thank you for it.

294
00:15:45.071 --> 00:15:46.406
Perhaps we should call her.

295
00:15:48.366 --> 00:15:51.035
She's probably got
a make-up problem or her dress.

296
00:15:51.077 --> 00:15:53.788
I know her.
She likes to look her best.

297
00:16:08.511 --> 00:16:10.013
Hey. sis.

298
00:16:10.054 --> 00:16:11.264
Hi. Robs.

299
00:16:11.306 --> 00:16:14.392
I just got off the phone
with Linda's mom.

300
00:16:14.434 --> 00:16:17.103
Linda's not there. but...

301
00:16:17.145 --> 00:16:18.271
there was a note.

302
00:16:18.313 --> 00:16:19.814
A note?

303
00:16:20.940 --> 00:16:22.567
Everything all right?

304
00:16:22.609 --> 00:16:25.069
Yeah. she's OK.

305
00:16:25.111 --> 00:16:27.530
It basically indicated...

306
00:16:27.572 --> 00:16:30.658
that Linda was...

307
00:16:30.700 --> 00:16:32.619
not coming today.

308
00:16:36.664 --> 00:16:39.167
So. it was a bad note.

309
00:16:40.502 --> 00:16:42.587
Did she say why?

310
00:16:46.090 --> 00:16:48.092
I am so sorry. honey.

311
00:16:49.135 --> 00:16:50.220
It's OK.

312
00:16:51.471 --> 00:16:52.972
You want me to say something?

313
00:16:55.934 --> 00:16:58.853
Just give me a second.
I'll be right back.

314
00:17:00.980 --> 00:17:02.982
Oh. my God.
she's not showing up.

315
00:17:15.036 --> 00:17:18.122
Don't worry.
Everything's gonna be all right.

316
00:17:18.164 --> 00:17:19.791
It's OK.

317
00:17:25.964 --> 00:17:27.465
Oh. God!

318
00:17:37.684 --> 00:17:39.811
You can't catch me!

319
00:17:39.853 --> 00:17:42.647
I'm going to get you
and chop you up!

320
00:17:42.689 --> 00:17:45.316
Can we turn this crap off.
please?

321
00:17:45.358 --> 00:17:48.319
That's right. Robbie.
You have to let it out.

322
00:17:48.361 --> 00:17:50.572
-Let what out?
-Your feelings.

323
00:17:50.613 --> 00:17:53.324
About what that lousy bitch
did to you today.

324
00:17:53.366 --> 00:17:54.409
Don't call her that...

325
00:17:54.450 --> 00:17:55.785
because we're going
to get back together...

326
00:17:55.827 --> 00:17:57.787
and then there will be weirdness
between you and me...

327
00:17:57.829 --> 00:17:59.914
so just watch it.

328
00:17:59.956 --> 00:18:02.083
I made this for you.
Uncle Robbie.

329
00:18:02.125 --> 00:18:04.377
Thanks. Freddy Krueger.

330
00:18:04.419 --> 00:18:06.713
That's not nice.

331
00:18:06.754 --> 00:18:08.882
Very creative. though.

332
00:18:08.923 --> 00:18:10.466
Go back to the boiler room.

333
00:18:12.218 --> 00:18:14.554
I just wish I knew
where she was. you know?

334
00:18:18.349 --> 00:18:19.893
He's taking it pretty bad.

335
00:18:19.934 --> 00:18:22.061
He's acting like a real robot...

336
00:18:22.103 --> 00:18:23.897
a zombie or something.

337
00:18:23.897 --> 00:18:26.816
He's been wanting to get married
since the third grade.

338
00:18:26.858 --> 00:18:29.527
It makes sense.
That's when Mom and Dad died.

339
00:18:29.569 --> 00:18:32.071
He wants to start
a family of his own.

340
00:18:32.071 --> 00:18:33.615
Check out the cake.

341
00:18:33.656 --> 00:18:36.409
There's only
a little groom on top.

342
00:18:56.387 --> 00:18:57.597
You're late.

343
00:18:57.639 --> 00:18:59.933
I'm sorry.

344
00:18:59.933 --> 00:19:01.559
I just couldn't do it.

345
00:19:03.895 --> 00:19:06.773
If you need some more time.
I guess I can wait.

346
00:19:08.441 --> 00:19:11.319
No. I don't need
more time. Robbie.

347
00:19:11.361 --> 00:19:12.737
I don't ever want to marry you.

348
00:19:17.283 --> 00:19:18.660
You know. that information...

349
00:19:18.701 --> 00:19:22.038
might have been a little
more useful to me yesterday.

350
00:19:23.957 --> 00:19:25.959
I've been talking to my friends
the last couple of days...

351
00:19:26.000 --> 00:19:27.794
Here it comes.

352
00:19:27.836 --> 00:19:31.422
And I think I figured out
what's been bothering me.

353
00:19:31.464 --> 00:19:33.591
I'm not in love with Robbie now.

354
00:19:33.633 --> 00:19:37.220
I'm in love with Robbie
six years ago...

355
00:19:37.262 --> 00:19:39.430
Robbie. the lead singer
of Final Warning...

356
00:19:39.472 --> 00:19:41.432
when I used to come and
watch you from the front row...

357
00:19:41.474 --> 00:19:43.601
in your spandex pants...

358
00:19:43.643 --> 00:19:45.770
your silk shirt unbuttoned...

359
00:19:47.146 --> 00:19:49.858
licking the microphone
like David Lee Roth.

360
00:19:49.899 --> 00:19:52.318
I still got the spandex.
I'll put them on right now.

361
00:19:52.360 --> 00:19:54.237
The point is.
I woke up this morning...

362
00:19:54.279 --> 00:19:57.615
and I realized I'm about
to marry a wedding singer.

363
00:19:57.657 --> 00:20:00.118
I am never going
to leave Ridgefield.

364
00:20:00.160 --> 00:20:02.078
Why do you need
to leave Ridgefield?

365
00:20:02.120 --> 00:20:05.165
We grew up here.
All our friends are here.

366
00:20:05.206 --> 00:20:07.333
It's the perfect place
to raise a family.

367
00:20:07.375 --> 00:20:09.878
Living in your sister's
basement with five kids...

368
00:20:09.919 --> 00:20:11.713
while you're off every
weekend doing wedding gigs...

369
00:20:11.754 --> 00:20:13.673
at a whopping 60 bucks a pop?

370
00:20:13.715 --> 00:20:15.216
Once again...

371
00:20:15.258 --> 00:20:17.177
things that could have been
brought to my attention...

372
00:20:17.177 --> 00:20:18.303
yesterday!

373
00:20:21.181 --> 00:20:23.433
The fact is.
we grew apart a long time ago.

374
00:20:24.601 --> 00:20:27.020
You wanted to get married.
You didn't care to who.

375
00:20:27.061 --> 00:20:30.273
That's not true. I love you.
Come here.

376
00:20:30.315 --> 00:20:33.818
I want to spend
the rest of my life with you.

377
00:20:33.860 --> 00:20:36.279
Hey. Linda.

378
00:20:36.321 --> 00:20:38.323
You're a bitch.

379
00:20:41.493 --> 00:20:44.037
Thanks. Petey.
Go back to the house.

380
00:20:46.956 --> 00:20:49.250
He might have
Tourette's syndrome.

381
00:20:49.292 --> 00:20:50.668
We're looking into it.

382
00:20:53.171 --> 00:20:54.464
I got to go.

383
00:20:57.550 --> 00:20:58.676
I'm sorry.

384
00:21:13.942 --> 00:21:16.486
Ninety-nine Luftballons...

385
00:21:19.531 --> 00:21:20.698
Glenn!

386
00:21:20.740 --> 00:21:22.951
Don't be so jumpy.

387
00:21:22.992 --> 00:21:25.203
These are for you.

388
00:21:25.245 --> 00:21:26.704
Thank you.

389
00:21:28.623 --> 00:21:30.708
They're beautiful.

390
00:21:32.168 --> 00:21:34.337
I have something else for you.

391
00:21:38.675 --> 00:21:41.636
Two airplane tickets
to Las Vegas?

392
00:21:45.515 --> 00:21:47.559
Oh. my God. Glenn!

393
00:21:49.227 --> 00:21:50.395
I know you wanted
to set a date...

394
00:21:50.436 --> 00:21:52.564
so I went to the travel agent
and set it.

395
00:21:53.940 --> 00:21:56.192
Glenn. I love you so much...

396
00:21:56.234 --> 00:21:57.360
but Las Vegas? I thought--

397
00:21:57.402 --> 00:21:59.445
Jules. it's the romance
capital of the world.

398
00:21:59.487 --> 00:22:02.073
I just don't want
a big wedding--

399
00:22:02.115 --> 00:22:03.783
hundreds of people
we don't know...

400
00:22:03.825 --> 00:22:05.827
that are just there
for the free drinks...

401
00:22:05.869 --> 00:22:07.912
and all-you-can-eat buffet.

402
00:22:07.954 --> 00:22:09.956
They might as well be in Vegas.

403
00:22:16.421 --> 00:22:19.549
Las Vegas it is.
and it'll be great.

404
00:22:21.301 --> 00:22:23.136
Are you going to do
the girl thing?

405
00:22:23.178 --> 00:22:26.472
You're going to act happy
and be pouting on the inside?

406
00:22:27.974 --> 00:22:29.642
I'm happy.

407
00:22:34.480 --> 00:22:35.815
All right.

408
00:22:35.815 --> 00:22:37.483
Let's get married here.

409
00:22:37.525 --> 00:22:40.403
I know that's what you want.

410
00:22:40.445 --> 00:22:42.322
Thank you. Glenn.

411
00:22:43.656 --> 00:22:45.158
It's more important
to you anyway.

412
00:22:46.659 --> 00:22:49.287
I promise I will give you
the most beautiful wedding...

413
00:22:49.329 --> 00:22:51.331
and even you'll have
a good time.

414
00:23:15.647 --> 00:23:18.149
It's about time
his best friend showed up.

415
00:23:18.191 --> 00:23:19.943
So. how's he doing?

416
00:23:19.984 --> 00:23:21.402
I don't know.

417
00:23:21.444 --> 00:23:24.489
He's been down in the basement
since it happened.

418
00:23:24.531 --> 00:23:26.533
Five days now.

419
00:23:26.533 --> 00:23:30.745
I think he's having some kind
of a mental situation...

420
00:23:30.787 --> 00:23:33.289
an episode or something.

421
00:23:33.331 --> 00:23:34.749
All right.

422
00:23:37.210 --> 00:23:39.170
You do something. because
I don't want to be known...

423
00:23:39.212 --> 00:23:41.464
as the brother-in-law
of the town nut job.

424
00:23:41.506 --> 00:23:42.924
I got enough problems already.

425
00:23:42.966 --> 00:23:45.134
Shit.
I got water all over myself.

426
00:23:53.935 --> 00:23:55.436
Hello?

427
00:24:00.817 --> 00:24:02.485
You all right?

428
00:24:10.160 --> 00:24:13.037
These sheets are soft.
You use Downy?

429
00:24:15.081 --> 00:24:17.417
All Tempa-Cheer.

430
00:24:17.417 --> 00:24:19.419
You can wash your clothes
at any temperature...

431
00:24:19.419 --> 00:24:21.421
and the colors
don't run together.

432
00:24:21.421 --> 00:24:24.674
-Really?
-Yeah. Now leave me alone.

433
00:24:26.259 --> 00:24:28.344
You have to go back to work.

434
00:24:28.386 --> 00:24:31.598
There's going to be over
a hundred drunk girls...

435
00:24:31.639 --> 00:24:32.765
at this wedding tonight.

436
00:24:32.807 --> 00:24:34.350
I've got nothing
to offer anybody.

437
00:24:34.392 --> 00:24:37.687
I haven't done jack shit
since high school.

438
00:24:37.729 --> 00:24:39.731
Why would any girl
ever marry me?

439
00:24:39.772 --> 00:24:41.482
Marry you?

440
00:24:41.524 --> 00:24:43.526
I'm just trying to get someone
to play with your ding-dong.

441
00:24:47.864 --> 00:24:49.949
Holiday...

442
00:24:52.118 --> 00:24:54.370
Celebrate...

443
00:25:05.340 --> 00:25:08.301
If we took a holiday...

444
00:25:09.677 --> 00:25:12.013
Took some time to celebrate...

445
00:25:12.055 --> 00:25:13.973
Come on. let's celebrate.

446
00:25:14.015 --> 00:25:16.559
Just one day out of life...

447
00:25:18.228 --> 00:25:20.438
It would be...

448
00:25:20.480 --> 00:25:23.816
It would be so nice.

449
00:25:23.816 --> 00:25:27.403
Everybody spread the word.

450
00:25:27.445 --> 00:25:31.741
I live in
my sister's basement.

451
00:25:32.909 --> 00:25:35.078
He just had his heart broken.

452
00:25:35.119 --> 00:25:37.914
Why would he even think
about coming back to work?

453
00:25:37.956 --> 00:25:39.582
I don't know.

454
00:25:39.624 --> 00:25:42.252
Celebrate.

455
00:25:53.429 --> 00:25:55.974
You guys are off
to a great start.

456
00:25:56.015 --> 00:25:57.517
I mean...

457
00:25:57.559 --> 00:26:00.228
Cindy showed up.
so. right away. Scott...

458
00:26:00.270 --> 00:26:01.688
you got to be pretty psyched.

459
00:26:03.106 --> 00:26:05.650
I'm not paying you to hear
your thoughts on life.

460
00:26:05.692 --> 00:26:07.026
I'm paying you to sing.

461
00:26:08.695 --> 00:26:12.198
I have a microphone.
and you don't...

462
00:26:12.240 --> 00:26:15.160
so you will listen
to every damn word...

463
00:26:15.201 --> 00:26:16.953
I have to say!

464
00:26:23.877 --> 00:26:28.339
It's funny. Some of us
will never find true love.

465
00:26:28.381 --> 00:26:32.135
Like. take. for instance...me.

466
00:26:33.344 --> 00:26:35.305
And I'm pretty sure
that guy right there.

467
00:26:37.473 --> 00:26:39.726
And that lady
with the sideburns.

468
00:26:41.603 --> 00:26:44.189
And basically
everybody at table nine.

469
00:26:45.607 --> 00:26:47.901
But the worst thing is...

470
00:26:47.901 --> 00:26:53.907
that me. fatty.
sideburns lady...

471
00:26:53.948 --> 00:26:55.742
and the mutants
over at table nine...

472
00:26:57.785 --> 00:27:01.080
will never. ever find a way
to better the situation...

473
00:27:01.080 --> 00:27:03.208
because...

474
00:27:03.249 --> 00:27:06.920
apparently. we have
absolutely nothing to offer...

475
00:27:06.961 --> 00:27:08.505
the opposite sex.

476
00:27:10.131 --> 00:27:12.592
You are the worst wedding singer
in the world. buddy!

477
00:27:12.634 --> 00:27:14.719
Sir. one more outburst...

478
00:27:14.761 --> 00:27:17.138
I will strangle you
with my microphone wire.

479
00:27:20.016 --> 00:27:21.809
Let's cut the stupid cake...

480
00:27:21.851 --> 00:27:23.770
because the fat guy's
going to have a heart attack...

481
00:27:23.811 --> 00:27:25.188
if we don't eat again soon.

482
00:27:27.524 --> 00:27:31.319
And while we do that.
here's a little mood music.

483
00:27:38.785 --> 00:27:41.412
Cindy and Scott are newlyweds.

484
00:27:47.168 --> 00:27:49.587
He loves her...

485
00:27:49.629 --> 00:27:52.257
But she loves
this guy right here...

486
00:27:52.298 --> 00:27:54.926
And he loves somebody else.

487
00:27:54.968 --> 00:27:57.887
You just can't win.

488
00:27:57.929 --> 00:27:59.889
And so it goes...

489
00:27:59.931 --> 00:28:02.851
Until the day you die.

490
00:28:02.892 --> 00:28:05.353
This thing they call love...

491
00:28:05.395 --> 00:28:07.647
Is gonna make you cry.

492
00:28:07.689 --> 00:28:08.857
I hate you.

493
00:28:08.898 --> 00:28:10.942
I've had the blues...

494
00:28:10.984 --> 00:28:13.778
The reds and the pinks.

495
00:28:13.820 --> 00:28:16.447
One thing's for sure...

496
00:28:17.490 --> 00:28:18.491
Love stinks?

497
00:28:18.491 --> 00:28:20.118
Love stinks.

498
00:28:42.056 --> 00:28:44.475
Drug addict! Degenerate!

499
00:29:12.837 --> 00:29:15.840
I was wondering
what happened to you.

500
00:29:17.759 --> 00:29:19.677
Did everybody leave?

501
00:29:20.887 --> 00:29:23.223
Pretty much.
except for a few cops...

502
00:29:23.264 --> 00:29:25.850
that are still interviewing
some witnesses.

503
00:29:30.647 --> 00:29:32.815
I'm going to get
the hell out of here.

504
00:29:34.984 --> 00:29:36.569
So it was
your first wedding back.

505
00:29:36.611 --> 00:29:38.947
Of course things are going
to be a little shaky.

506
00:29:38.988 --> 00:29:41.533
A little shaky?
I hate weddings.

507
00:29:41.574 --> 00:29:44.786
I hate the bride.
I hate the groom.

508
00:29:44.828 --> 00:29:47.872
I want them to be miserable.
because that's what I am.

509
00:29:47.914 --> 00:29:49.916
No. You're the best.

510
00:29:49.916 --> 00:29:53.503
At what? People eat
prime rib. and I sing.

511
00:29:53.545 --> 00:29:57.048
It's a joke.
I can't do this anymore.

512
00:29:58.049 --> 00:30:00.927
Glenn and I set the date...

513
00:30:00.969 --> 00:30:02.929
so you have to play our wedding.

514
00:30:05.056 --> 00:30:06.558
Congratulations.

515
00:30:07.809 --> 00:30:11.896
I just can't do it. all right?

516
00:30:12.939 --> 00:30:15.400
I'm having an engagement party
in two weeks...

517
00:30:15.441 --> 00:30:17.652
and I really want
you and Sammy to come.

518
00:30:39.174 --> 00:30:41.176
Good. you're here.

519
00:30:41.217 --> 00:30:43.678
Robbie's here!
Let's move it!

520
00:30:43.720 --> 00:30:45.597
The kids have been fed.
but if they want snacks...

521
00:30:45.638 --> 00:30:48.975
there's ice pops in the freezer.
or microwave popcorn.

