01:17:08.880 --> 01:17:10.924
What are you doing?

1281
01:17:10.965 --> 01:17:12.967
I'm sorry.

1282
01:17:13.009 --> 01:17:15.178
I used to be much stronger.

1283
01:17:23.102 --> 01:17:24.729
Why don't you write
a song about this?

1284
01:17:24.771 --> 01:17:26.189
You can call it...

1285
01:17:26.231 --> 01:17:28.900
"l got punched in the nose...

1286
01:17:28.942 --> 01:17:31.444
"for stickin' my face
in other people's business."

1287
01:17:35.990 --> 01:17:37.826
Way to go.

1288
01:17:37.867 --> 01:17:40.370
Sounds like a country song.

1289
01:17:55.593 --> 01:17:58.388
Kiss my grits.

1290
01:18:04.561 --> 01:18:09.274
I can see that you're drunk.
and that's OK.

1291
01:18:09.315 --> 01:18:11.484
I'm still gonna tell you this.

1292
01:18:11.526 --> 01:18:14.028
I really miss you.
and I want to come back.

1293
01:18:15.697 --> 01:18:17.824
I don't want
to be alone anymore.

1294
01:18:19.826 --> 01:18:22.078
You're not alone anymore.

1295
01:18:22.120 --> 01:18:23.913
Linda's back.

1296
01:19:07.874 --> 01:19:10.084
Can I help you?

1297
01:19:13.505 --> 01:19:14.797
Is Robbie here?

1298
01:19:16.633 --> 01:19:18.635
I'm afraid he's indisposed.

1299
01:19:22.430 --> 01:19:23.598
Shower.

1300
01:19:28.102 --> 01:19:29.646
You must be Linda.

1301
01:19:29.687 --> 01:19:33.149
Yeah. that's me...
Robbie's fiancee.

1302
01:19:33.191 --> 01:19:35.151
Who are you?

1303
01:19:35.193 --> 01:19:36.444
I'm Julia Sullivan.

1304
01:19:38.488 --> 01:19:40.824
Would you tell him
that I came by to see him?

1305
01:19:40.865 --> 01:19:43.201
Oh. yeah.
surely will. Jennifer.

1306
01:19:43.243 --> 01:19:44.619
It's Julia.

1307
01:20:02.137 --> 01:20:04.806
Wake up. sleepyhead.

1308
01:20:04.848 --> 01:20:07.725
This is the first day
of our new life together.

1309
01:20:10.145 --> 01:20:11.271
Wake me up...

1310
01:20:11.312 --> 01:20:13.273
Before you go-go.

1311
01:20:13.314 --> 01:20:17.277
Don't leave me hanging on
like a solo.

1312
01:20:28.621 --> 01:20:29.873
What are you doing here?

1313
01:20:31.624 --> 01:20:35.420
Well. you passed out.
so I took care of you.

1314
01:20:35.461 --> 01:20:37.922
What?
Why'd you take care of me?

1315
01:20:39.632 --> 01:20:42.760
I told you last night.
I realized I was wrong...

1316
01:20:42.802 --> 01:20:44.929
and I want to take
care of you for good.

1317
01:20:44.971 --> 01:20:46.097
I can learn
to deal with the fact...

1318
01:20:46.139 --> 01:20:49.434
that you're a wedding singer
and not a rock star.

1319
01:20:49.476 --> 01:20:51.269
You can learn to deal with that?

1320
01:20:51.311 --> 01:20:54.314
I don't want you to learn
to deal with that.

1321
01:20:54.314 --> 01:20:57.484
That's not how it works. Jeez!

1322
01:21:00.487 --> 01:21:03.072
Maybe we should talk about this
when you're feeling better.

1323
01:21:03.114 --> 01:21:05.450
Hey. psycho...

1324
01:21:05.492 --> 01:21:07.285
I'm not gonna feel
better about this.

1325
01:21:07.327 --> 01:21:09.078
It's over.

1326
01:21:09.120 --> 01:21:11.456
Now please get out
of my Van Halen t-shirt...

1327
01:21:11.498 --> 01:21:13.791
before you jinx the band
and they break up.

1328
01:21:18.505 --> 01:21:20.757
So you're still pissed
about that wedding thing.

1329
01:21:33.978 --> 01:21:35.021
Glenn. good morning.

1330
01:21:39.984 --> 01:21:42.111
Hey. baby.

1331
01:21:42.153 --> 01:21:44.197
You gonna make breakfast in bed?

1332
01:21:45.907 --> 01:21:48.701
Actually. I've been doing
some thinking. and...

1333
01:21:50.203 --> 01:21:52.330
I don't need a big wedding...

1334
01:21:52.372 --> 01:21:54.582
and I think
that I've been really selfish...

1335
01:21:54.624 --> 01:21:58.086
making you do something
you don't even want to do.

1336
01:22:00.547 --> 01:22:02.048
You wanna go to Vegas?

1337
01:22:05.343 --> 01:22:07.971
All right. Let's go.

1338
01:22:10.557 --> 01:22:13.852
There were bells...

1339
01:22:13.893 --> 01:22:16.896
On a hill...

1340
01:22:16.938 --> 01:22:22.652
But I never heard them ringing.

1341
01:22:22.694 --> 01:22:27.157
No. I never heard
them at all...

1342
01:22:27.198 --> 01:22:32.704
'Til there was you.

1343
01:22:34.205 --> 01:22:38.960
And there was music...

1344
01:22:39.002 --> 01:22:44.132
And there were wonderful roses.

1345
01:22:44.174 --> 01:22:47.051
They tell me...

1346
01:22:47.093 --> 01:22:49.053
In sweet...

1347
01:22:49.095 --> 01:22:52.724
Fragrant meadows...

1348
01:22:52.765 --> 01:22:59.772
Of dawn and dew.

1349
01:22:59.814 --> 01:23:02.358
There was love...

1350
01:23:02.400 --> 01:23:03.401
All around...

1351
01:23:03.443 --> 01:23:07.280
Flight number 1156
is now ready for boarding.

1352
01:23:07.322 --> 01:23:11.826
We'd like to ask passengers
traveling with small children...

1353
01:23:11.868 --> 01:23:16.915
I never heard it at all...

1354
01:23:16.956 --> 01:23:23.796
'Til there was you.

1355
01:23:23.838 --> 01:23:25.715
I just always
envisioned the right one...

1356
01:23:25.757 --> 01:23:27.967
being someone
I could grow old with.

1357
01:23:34.766 --> 01:23:37.185
I know. I'll go get the car.

1358
01:23:38.645 --> 01:23:41.189
Rosie. congratulations.

1359
01:23:41.231 --> 01:23:42.565
I gotta go take care
of something. OK?

1360
01:23:42.607 --> 01:23:45.276
I know you do. Go get her.

1361
01:23:45.318 --> 01:23:47.278
All right.

1362
01:23:47.320 --> 01:23:48.863
-l need to talk to you.
-l can't talk right now.

1363
01:23:48.905 --> 01:23:52.116
-Are you back with Linda?
-No. Who said that?

1364
01:23:52.158 --> 01:23:54.744
Julia.
She went to your house...

1365
01:23:54.786 --> 01:23:56.621
to tell you she was
falling for you...

1366
01:23:56.663 --> 01:23:58.665
and Linda answered the door
in her underwear.

1367
01:23:58.665 --> 01:24:00.041
She was so upset...

1368
01:24:00.083 --> 01:24:01.918
she and Glenn
jumped a plane to Vegas.

1369
01:24:01.960 --> 01:24:04.087
What do you mean? They're
getting married tomorrow.

1370
01:24:04.128 --> 01:24:06.422
Apparently.
that wasn't soon enough.

1371
01:24:08.591 --> 01:24:09.592
I said. hip. hop...

1372
01:24:09.676 --> 01:24:11.761
A-hippie to the hippie
to the hip. hip. hop.

1373
01:24:11.803 --> 01:24:13.972
You don't stop rockin'
to the bang. bang boogie...

1374
01:24:14.013 --> 01:24:15.265
Say. up comes the boogie...

1375
01:24:15.306 --> 01:24:16.724
To the rhythm
of the boogie that beats.

1376
01:24:16.766 --> 01:24:18.768
We're now ready
for our general boarding.

1377
01:24:18.852 --> 01:24:20.687
That's it. sweetie.
Ready to go?

1378
01:24:22.647 --> 01:24:25.733
This is a great idea.
I'm glad you came around.

1379
01:24:25.775 --> 01:24:27.777
You want to do some
gambling and fun right away...

1380
01:24:27.819 --> 01:24:28.987
or just get married?

1381
01:24:29.028 --> 01:24:30.905
I just want to get married.

1382
01:24:30.947 --> 01:24:32.824
You're never going to find her.

1383
01:24:32.866 --> 01:24:35.034
There's got to be a million
wedding chapels in Vegas.

1384
01:24:35.076 --> 01:24:37.245
-Does anybody have a pen?
-What for?

1385
01:24:37.287 --> 01:24:38.788
I got a good idea for a song.

1386
01:24:38.830 --> 01:24:41.291
-Here.
-Thank you.

1387
01:24:46.337 --> 01:24:47.547
Thank you.

1388
01:24:47.589 --> 01:24:48.631
Hey. I'm sorry.

1389
01:24:48.673 --> 01:24:50.341
Can I help you?

1390
01:24:50.383 --> 01:24:52.343
I need a ticket
for Las Vegas. please.

1391
01:24:54.262 --> 01:24:57.348
We only have one seat left
in our first-class section.

1392
01:24:57.390 --> 01:24:58.850
The next flight
leaves in the morning.

1393
01:25:00.226 --> 01:25:02.479
Can I borrow
your credit card?

1394
01:25:02.520 --> 01:25:04.355
You're going
to pay me back. right?

1395
01:25:04.397 --> 01:25:06.399
No. but if you don't
give it to me...

1396
01:25:06.441 --> 01:25:10.111
I'm going to tell everybody
what you said at the bar.

1397
01:25:10.153 --> 01:25:11.321
Thanks.

1398
01:25:11.362 --> 01:25:13.531
That was really nice of you.

1399
01:25:13.573 --> 01:25:14.741
Thanks.

1400
01:25:14.782 --> 01:25:16.743
Do you like
Flock of Seagulls?

1401
01:25:16.784 --> 01:25:19.037
I can see you do.

1402
01:25:19.078 --> 01:25:20.538
-Wish me luck.
-Go get her!

1403
01:25:32.217 --> 01:25:33.551
Do you mind
if we switched seats...

1404
01:25:33.593 --> 01:25:35.011
and I sat in the window seat?

1405
01:25:36.971 --> 01:25:38.556
I hate the aisle seat.

1406
01:25:38.598 --> 01:25:41.351
Every time that cart comes by.
it bangs me in the elbows.

1407
01:25:41.392 --> 01:25:45.355
Your arms are smaller
than mine. Jules.

1408
01:25:45.396 --> 01:25:49.567
I know. I just never saw
the lights of Vegas before.

1409
01:25:51.361 --> 01:25:52.862
Tell you what.

1410
01:25:52.904 --> 01:25:55.532
How about I let you lean over me
when we fly over the strip?

1411
01:26:04.040 --> 01:26:05.542
Thank you.

1412
01:26:06.793 --> 01:26:07.961
Hot towel?

1413
01:26:10.380 --> 01:26:12.257
Thanks.

1414
01:26:21.891 --> 01:26:24.644
Oh. my. I'm sorry.

1415
01:26:25.812 --> 01:26:27.939
I've never been
on first class before.

1416
01:26:27.981 --> 01:26:30.358
My name is Joyce.
Just buzz if you need anything.

1417
01:26:30.400 --> 01:26:32.610
Thank you. Here.

1418
01:26:37.490 --> 01:26:39.284
Sir?

1419
01:26:39.325 --> 01:26:40.785
Is that Billy Idol?

1420
01:26:42.537 --> 01:26:44.789
-I believe it is.
-Oh. my God.

1421
01:26:44.831 --> 01:26:47.500
Would you like some champagne
or some orange juice?

1422
01:26:47.542 --> 01:26:49.169
How much is it?

1423
01:26:49.210 --> 01:26:52.297
-It's free.
-It's what?

1424
01:26:52.338 --> 01:26:54.549
Holy shit. this is incredible.

1425
01:26:54.591 --> 01:26:55.842
Actually. I shouldn't drink.

1426
01:26:55.884 --> 01:26:59.053
I fell in love with this girl
who's going to marry an idiot...

1427
01:26:59.095 --> 01:27:01.097
so I'm on my way to Vegas
to stop them.

1428
01:27:01.181 --> 01:27:04.601
That's the sweetest thing
I've ever heard.

1429
01:27:04.642 --> 01:27:06.019
Where are they getting married?

1430
01:27:06.060 --> 01:27:07.061
I don't know where...

1431
01:27:07.103 --> 01:27:08.855
but I'm going to run around
and find them.

1432
01:27:08.897 --> 01:27:10.356
I got to do what I got to do.

1433
01:27:21.034 --> 01:27:22.660
Next time they come by.
grab me a Heineken.

1434
01:27:30.877 --> 01:27:32.670
She comes over to tell me
how she feels...

1435
01:27:32.712 --> 01:27:34.714
and Linda answers the door...

1436
01:27:34.714 --> 01:27:37.217
wearing nothing
but my Van Halen t-shirt.

1437
01:27:37.258 --> 01:27:38.843
No way.

1438
01:27:38.885 --> 01:27:40.094
I don't know what to do.

1439
01:27:40.136 --> 01:27:42.639
She's getting married.
and he's going to ruin her life.

1440
01:27:42.680 --> 01:27:44.933
Glenn doesn't deserve her.

1441
01:27:44.974 --> 01:27:47.060
All he cares about
are possessions...

1442
01:27:47.101 --> 01:27:51.064
fancy cars. CD players.

1443
01:27:51.105 --> 01:27:53.566
Even women
are possessions to him.

1444
01:27:53.608 --> 01:27:54.734
Billy idol gets it.

1445
01:27:54.776 --> 01:27:56.653
I don't know why
she doesn't get it.

1446
01:27:56.694 --> 01:27:57.946
I hope you find her.

1447
01:27:57.987 --> 01:27:59.656
You guys
will not believe this.

1448
01:27:59.697 --> 01:28:01.741
Some creep in coach
who thinks he's Don Johnson...

1449
01:28:01.783 --> 01:28:04.536
just asked me to be part
of the mile-high club.

1450
01:28:04.577 --> 01:28:08.206
He said I was
Grade-A. top-choice meat.

1451
01:28:14.254 --> 01:28:15.880
Is he right in here?

1452
01:28:17.924 --> 01:28:19.384
What's the mile-high club?

1453
01:28:29.602 --> 01:28:31.479
Oh. my God.
The mile-high guy is Glenn.

1454
01:28:31.521 --> 01:28:32.981
They're on this plane.

1455
01:28:33.022 --> 01:28:34.691
No way!

1456
01:28:34.732 --> 01:28:35.859
You guys got to help me.

1457
01:28:35.900 --> 01:28:37.569
Right!

1458
01:28:40.780 --> 01:28:42.866
Good afternoon. everyone.

1459
01:28:42.907 --> 01:28:46.661
We're flying at 26.000 feet.
moving up to 30.000 feet...

1460
01:28:46.703 --> 01:28:50.039
and we got clear skies
all the way to Las Vegas.

1461
01:28:50.081 --> 01:28:53.251
And now. we're bringing you
some in-flight entertainment.

1462
01:28:53.293 --> 01:28:55.253
One of our first-class
passengers...

1463
01:28:55.295 --> 01:28:56.713
would like
to sing you a song...

1464
01:28:56.754 --> 01:28:58.715
inspired by one
of our coach passengers.

1465
01:28:58.756 --> 01:29:01.718
And since we let
our first-class passengers...

1466
01:29:01.801 --> 01:29:05.430
do pretty much whatever
they want. here he is.

1467
01:29:07.640 --> 01:29:11.019
I wanna make you smile...

1468
01:29:11.060 --> 01:29:13.438
Whenever you're sad...

1469
01:29:13.480 --> 01:29:14.731
Carry you around...

1470
01:29:14.772 --> 01:29:17.317
When your arthritis is bad.

1471
01:29:17.358 --> 01:29:20.069
Oh. all I wanna do...

1472
01:29:20.111 --> 01:29:22.780
Is grow old with you.

1473
01:29:25.783 --> 01:29:27.869
I'll get you medicine...

1474
01:29:27.911 --> 01:29:31.456
When your tummy aches...

1475
01:29:31.498 --> 01:29:33.082
Build you a fire...

1476
01:29:33.124 --> 01:29:35.126
If the furnace breaks.

1477
01:29:35.168 --> 01:29:38.797
Oh. it could be so nice...

1478
01:29:38.838 --> 01:29:41.466
Growin' old with you.

1479
01:29:44.469 --> 01:29:46.554
I'll miss you...

1480
01:29:46.596 --> 01:29:48.848
Kiss you...

1481
01:29:48.890 --> 01:29:50.558
Give you my coat...

1482
01:29:50.600 --> 01:29:53.102
When you are cold...

1483
01:29:53.186 --> 01:29:55.104
Need you...

1484
01:29:55.146 --> 01:29:57.440
Feed you...

1485
01:29:57.482 --> 01:29:59.108
Even let you hold...

1486
01:29:59.150 --> 01:30:01.152
The remote control.

1487
01:30:05.031 --> 01:30:07.033
What the hell's
that fruit doing here?

1488
01:30:12.121 --> 01:30:13.915
Get out of the way!

1489
01:30:13.957 --> 01:30:15.792
Excuse me. sir.
I have to serve the beverages.

1490
01:30:23.216 --> 01:30:25.885
How you doing. sir?
Chicken or fish?

1491
01:30:25.927 --> 01:30:27.387
Get out of my way.
or you're going to get hurt.

1492
01:30:28.596 --> 01:30:31.099
Don't you talk
to Billy Idol that way.

1493
01:30:35.228 --> 01:30:37.188
So let me clear the dishes...

1494
01:30:37.230 --> 01:30:40.275
In our kitchen sink...

1495
01:30:40.316 --> 01:30:41.442
Put you to bed...

1496
01:30:41.484 --> 01:30:43.695
When you've had
too much to drink.

1497
01:30:46.114 --> 01:30:48.658
I could be the man...

1498
01:30:48.700 --> 01:30:52.871
Who grows old with you.

1499
01:30:52.912 --> 01:30:55.415
I wanna grow old...

1500
01:30:55.456 --> 01:30:57.750
With you.

1501
01:31:06.634 --> 01:31:09.262
That was the most
beautiful song.

1502
01:31:09.304 --> 01:31:11.014
I got a confession to make.

1503
01:31:11.055 --> 01:31:13.850
That song was about you.

1504
01:31:13.892 --> 01:31:15.351
Good.

1505
01:31:15.393 --> 01:31:17.687
I'm in love with you.

1506
01:31:19.189 --> 01:31:21.941
I am so in love with you.

1507
01:31:23.985 --> 01:31:25.695
That wasn't a bad song.

1508
01:31:25.737 --> 01:31:28.198
I'm going to tell those
record company guys about you.

1509
01:31:28.239 --> 01:31:30.492
You mind if I give her
a kiss first?

1510
01:31:30.533 --> 01:31:32.577
Do what you got to do.

1511
01:31:52.555 --> 01:31:55.266
I know this...

1512
01:31:55.308 --> 01:31:57.101
Much is...

1513
01:31:57.143 --> 01:31:58.436
True.

1514
01:32:02.190 --> 01:32:04.984
I know this...

1515
01:32:05.026 --> 01:32:06.861
Much is...

1516
01:32:06.903 --> 01:32:08.696
True.

1517
01:32:09.697 --> 01:32:11.533
I know. I know. I know...

1518
01:32:11.574 --> 01:32:14.077
This much is true.

1519
01:32:14.118 --> 01:32:16.371
Oh. yes. I do...

1520
01:32:16.412 --> 01:32:20.542
Robbie and Julia.

1521
01:32:21.305 --> 01:33:21.328
Do you want subtitles for any video?
